Name: errno
License File: LICENSE-APACHE
License File: LICENSE-MIT
Description: Cross-platform interface to the `errno` variable.

* What is this crate used for?
Cross-platform system error number retrieval and handling.

* Are there any use restrictions? i.e. only for development hosts
No.

* What differs from upstream? Include a changelog if feasible.
Added `target_os = "fuchsia"` to the `__errno_location` symbol link attribute in `src/unix.rs`.
On Fuchsia's C library (musl), `errno` location is provided by `__errno_location`. Upstream `errno`
lacks `target_os = "fuchsia"` in this attribute arm,
causing `lld: error: undefined symbol: errno_location`.
An upstream pull request is at https://github.com/lambda-fairy/rust-errno/pull/126.
When it has been merged into a release, this can be un-forked and the new version should move back
into vendor/.

* Are there any restrictions to how it should be rolled?
When rolling upstream versions, ensure `target_os = "fuchsia"` is preserved on `__errno_location`
unless upstream has merged Fuchsia support.

* Is there anything else which makes this dependency "special"?
No.
